# Info
Invoked on the client side when the player connects to a server or loads a singleplayer world. This is useful for running client-side initialization logic when joining a world.

# Available Event Fields
- `event.player` - the local player that logged in (`LocalPlayer`)

# Example

```js
ClientEvents.loggedIn(event => {
	console.log('Connected to server!')
	console.log('Player name: ' + event.player.name.string)
})
```
